{
  "files": [
    {"repo": "kubernetes/kubernetes", "path": "staging/src/k8s.io/api/core/v1/types.go"},
    {"repo": "kubernetes/kubernetes", "path": "staging/src/k8s.io/api/core/v1/annotation_key_constants.go"},
    {"repo": "kubernetes/kubernetes", "path": "staging/src/k8s.io/api/discovery/v1/types.go"},
    {"repo": "kubernetes/kubernetes", "path": "staging/src/k8s.io/api/events/v1/types.go"},
    {"repo": "kubernetes/kubernetes", "path": "staging/src/k8s.io/api/events/v1beta1/types.go"},
    {"repo": "kubernetes/kubernetes", "path": "pkg/apis/core/annotation_key_constants.go"},
    {"repo": "kubernetes/kubernetes", "path": "pkg/apis/discovery/types.go"}
  ],
  "text": "The Kubernetes API contains several deprecated struct fields and constants that are still defined but should be phased out. In the staging/src/k8s.io/api/ (public API types) and pkg/apis/ (internal API types) directories:\n\nDeprecated struct fields include: DeprecatedServiceAccount in Pod specs (core/v1/types.go), DeprecatedTopology in EndpointSlice specifications (discovery/v1/types.go and pkg/apis/discovery/types.go), and deprecated event fields DeprecatedSource, DeprecatedFirstTimestamp, DeprecatedLastTimestamp, and DeprecatedCount for backward compatibility with core.v1 Event types (events/v1/types.go and events/v1beta1/types.go).\n\nDeprecated annotation constants are defined in two annotation_key_constants.go files: DeprecatedSeccompProfileDockerDefault (used for docker default seccomp profile), DeprecatedAppArmorAnnotationKeyPrefix and related AppArmor annotation constants (DeprecatedAppArmorAnnotationValueRuntimeDefault, DeprecatedAppArmorAnnotationValueLocalhostPrefix, DeprecatedAppArmorAnnotationValueUnconfined) in pkg/apis/core, and their v1 API variants (DeprecatedAppArmorBetaContainerAnnotationKeyPrefix, DeprecatedAppArmorBetaProfileRuntimeDefault, DeprecatedAppArmorBetaProfileNamePrefix, DeprecatedAppArmorBetaProfileNameUnconfined) in staging/src/k8s.io/api/core/v1. Additionally, DeprecatedAnnotationTopologyAwareHints is defined in both locations for topology-aware hints configuration (now superseded by AnnotationTopologyMode). These deprecated fields and constants maintain backward compatibility with older client code and cluster configurations while users migrate to the recommended replacements."
}

